OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1783871341
OL,3,CHeatwave to last until next week as
OL,4,Cemergency services warn of wildfire
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FThe Metropolitan Police has also said
OL,8,Fit is worried about excessive calls,
OL,9,Fwith England set to play Norway in a
OL,10,Fquarter-final of the Fifa World Cup on
OL,11,FSaturday night.
OL,13,FThe Met has urged people to avoid
OL,14,Fgetting in touch for non-emergencies
OL,15,Famid a surge in 999 calls during the
OL,16,Fhot weather.
OL,18,FForecasters have said areas of England
OL,19,Fand Wales will continue to exceed 30C
OL,20,Fthroughout the weekend and into next
OL,21,Fweek.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1783871341
OL,3,CHeatwave to last until next week as
OL,4,Cemergency services warn of wildfire
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FSaturday is expected to see highs of
OL,8,F32-34C in Wales and south-west
OL,9,FEngland, the Met Office has said.
OL,11,FAmber and yellow heat health alerts
OL,12,Fissued by the UK Health Security
OL,13,FAgency will remain in place across
OL,14,Flarge parts of England until 9pm on
OL,15,FWednesday.
OL,17,FThe Met Office has warned of possible
OL,18,Fthunderstorms from Monday in parts of
OL,19,Fthe south, but said overall another
OL,20,Fvery dry week is set to come.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
