PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1783871341
OL,3,CHeatwave to last until next week as
OL,4,Cemergency services warn of wildfire
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FMet Office deputy chief forecaster
OL,8,FDavid Hayter said: "Areas of central
OL,9,Fand southern England and Wales are
OL,10,Fexpected to see several more
OL,11,Fconsecutive days of temperatures above
OL,12,F30C.
OL,14,F"While temperatures are expected to
OL,15,Freach into the low to mid-30s through
OL,16,Fthe weekend, the focus of the heat
OL,17,Fwill gradually shift towards western
OL,18,Fparts of the UK.
OL,26,@pD@TOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1783871341
OL,3,CHeatwave to last until next week as
OL,4,Cemergency services warn of wildfire
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,F"This will also bring some slightly
OL,8,Fcooler and cloudier conditions to
OL,9,Feastern coastal areas than of recent
OL,10,Fdays."
OL,12,FThe Met Office announced the new
OL,13,Frecords after temperatures peaked at
OL,14,F35.2C at Coton in the Elms,
OL,15,FDerbyshire, on Friday afternoon.
OL,17,FLater in the evening, Derbyshire Fire
OL,18,Fand Rescue (DFR) confirmed that it was
OL,19,Fcurrently fighting two wildfires in
OL,20,Fthe area.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
